[SN]TITLE[SN]
What to do if you're being bullied

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
As part of national Anti-Bullying week Newsround has been asking kids about the best way to stop it.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
20 November 2015 Last updated at 14:22 GMT
A special vote was launched on the CBBC website to see if kids think it's better to help bullies or punish them.
More than 2, 400 children voted and 47% thought that bullies should be punished for their actions, with 53% saying bullies should be helped.
We spoke to Alex Holmes, who is an anti bullying specialist, to get his advice for anyone who is being bullied.
